[2026-03-09 16:26:01] [1d5c3289-82f5-47bd-941c-b7c9d068124c] CLAUDE: All 17 tests pass, lint/typecheck/build clean.  **Root cause**: Google Meet puts `data-message-id` on **two** elements per message — the message `<div class="RLrADb">` and the pin `<button>` inside it. The selector `[data-message-id]` matched both, causing double processing.  **Fix**: Changed the selector to `div[data-message-id]` (exported as `MESSAGE_SELECTOR` from `dom.ts`) so only the actual message divs are matched, not the pin buttons. Used consistently in `dom.ts`, `console.ts`, and tests. 
